task-odors_bold.json.TaskName: TODO: full task name for odors
Description: Four odorants with previously-verified iso-intense perception were used.In each of two functional runs, 10 stimuli per valence were delivered, culminating in 20 pleasant and 20 unpleasant odorant events in both runs. Stimulus duration = 3 sec, interstimulus-interval = 20-26 sec (jittered), odourant onset triggered by ihalation onset. Participants were instructed to breathe naturally, to keep their eyes closed, and if they noted an odorant, to rate its pleasantness using a button box placed in their dominant (left) hand.

Levels.smelly-cheese: isovaleric acid CAS no. 503-74-2, from Sigma-Aldrich, Israel
Levels.banana: oil from from Frutarom Inc. Israel

response.Description: Subjective pleasantness ratings following an odor delivery

README:
Functional MRI paradigm and analysis:
In each of two functional runs, 10 stimuli per valence were delivered, culminatingin 20 pleasant and 20 unpleasant odourant events in both runs. Stimulus duration = 3 sec, ISI = 20-26 sec (jittered), odourant onset triggered by inhalation onset.
Thus, the duration in the event files is the duration of the first sniff. 

sub-05_task-odors_run-02: Subject fell asleep in the end of the run, thus the time course was trim (29 dicoms), and the last trial was excluded.
sub-08: sometimes press too weak on the buttons, so the response was not recorded.
sub-09_task-odors_run-02: skip the first 60 dicoms due to sharp head movement (translation in Y direction > 4mm).
sub-11: many times she did not press because felling asleep
sub-15: excluded from the analysis due to atypical hemodynamic response.
sub-12, sub-16: due to technical error the odour bacon was delivered instead of smelly-cheese.
sub-18_task-odors_run-02 confused with the ratings, thus we applied n/a
